NATIONAL LABOR RELATIONS BOARD, Petitioner, v. ALASKAN GLACIER SEA FOOD COMPANY, a Corporation, Respondent. No. 9119. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 13, 1939. Charles Fahy, Gen. Counsel, and Robert B. Watts, Associate Gen. Counsel, both of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. N. C. Banfield, of Juneau, Alaska, and James J. Molthan, of Seattle, Wash., for respondent.

Before GARRECHT, HANEY, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered petition to enforce granted, and a decree filed and' entered accordingly.
